parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Fuel Filler Tube and Left Rear Fender
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the fuel filler tube and left rear fender can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, and exhaust fumes can leak into the cabin, posing a risk of carbon monoxide poisoning.
symptoms: corrosion of fuel filler tube and left rear fender

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel injector failure can cause fuel leaks, oil leakage, and fire potential, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: fuel injectors need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Train Axle Failure due to Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power train axle can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud clanking noise coming from the left front of the vehicle
corrosion on the power train axle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: transmission blew out on multiple occasions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rollaway Due to Transmission or Parking Brake Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission or parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll away, leading to accidents or property damage.
symptoms: Vehicle rolls away when parked on an incline with the ignition off

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer can cause the driver to be unaware of their speed, leading to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: Speedometer no longer reads 100% of the time

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to be unaware of important vehicle information, leading to accidents or property damage.
symptoms: Windshield speedometer display failed to appear at start-up

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the digital dashboard can cause the driver to be unaware of important vehicle information, such as speed, fuel level, and engine performance, which can lead to accidents or safety risks.
symptoms: Horizontal streaks or lines appear on the dashboard display
readings flicker or go out completely
dashboard lights do not turn on
and other essential readings are not displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the dashboard computer to malfunction, leading to a loss of essential vehicle information and potentially causing accidents or safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A vehicle fire can cause serious damage to the vehicle and potentially harm the occupants.
